sh, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Lucy","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish and English: variant of   Lucey  .","French: habitational name from any of various places called Lucy, originally named with the Latin personal name <i>Lucius</i> + the locative suffix <i>-acum</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Lucey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Maeve, Niall.","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Luasaigh</b>, an altered form of <b>Mac Cluasaigh</b>, a Cork name meaning ‘son of <i>Cluasach</i>’, a byname originally denoting someone with large or otherwise noticeable ears (from <i>cluas</i> ‘ear’).","English: variant of   Luce   1."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William de Lucy was born about 1260, in Charlecote, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Fouk De Lucy Knight, was 22 and his mother, Mrs. Petronella De Lucy, was 20. He married Elizabeth Of Charlecote about 1289. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1359, at the age of 100."},"et":{"Abt 1260–1359":"umbes 1260–1359","1260–1359":"1260–1359","1293–Female":"1293–Surnud","1264–Female":"1264–Surnud","1290–1348":"1290–1348","1340–Female":"1340–Surnud","1353–Male":"1353–Surnud","1355–1374":"1355–1374","1353–1401":"1353–1401","1240–1302":"1240–1302","1242–Female":"1242–Surnud","1242":"1242","1374":"1374","1264":"1264","1340":"1340","1240":"1240","1293":"1293","1260":"1260","1290":"1290","abt 1302":"umbes 1302","1348":"1348","1359":"1359","Abt 1260":"umbes 1260","1302":"1302","1401":"1401","1355":"1355","ABT 1289":"umbes 1289","1353":"1353","ABT 1290":"umbes 1290",", Charlecote, Warwickshire, England":"Charlecote, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Charlecote, Warwickshire, England":"Charlecote, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Of, Charlecote, Warwickshire, England":"Charlecote, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1260–1359":"noin 1260–1359","1260–1359":"1260–1359","1293–Female":"1293–Kuollut","1264–Female":"1264–Kuollut","1290–1348":"1290–1348","1340–Female":"1340–Kuollut","1353–Male":"1353–Kuollut","1355–1374":"1355–1374","1353–1401":"1353–1401","1240–1302":"1240–1302","1242–Female":"1242–Kuollut","1242":"1242","1374":"1374","1264":"1264","1340":"1340","1240":"1240","1293":"1293","1260":"1260","1290":"1290","abt 1302":"noin 1302","1348":"1348","1359":"1359","Abt 1260":"noin 1260","1302":"1302","1401":"1401","1355":"1355","ABT 1289":"noin 1289","1353":"1353","ABT 1290":"noin 1290",", Charlecote, Warwickshire, England":"Charlecote, Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Charlecote, Warwickshire, England":"Charlecote, Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Of, Charlecote, Warwickshire, England":"Charlecote, Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1260–1359":"environ 1260–1359","1260–1359":"1260–1359","1293–Female":"1293–Décédée","1264–Female":"1264–Décédée","1290–1348":"1290–1348","1340–Female":"1340–Décédée","1353–Male":"1353–